The underlying differential cross-section distributions are obtained from the detector-level events using an unfolding technique that corrects for detector effects. The iterative Bayesian method [57] as implemented in RooUnfold [58] is used. The individual \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
