The SM predictions are obtained using different MC generators. The Powheg-Box generator [17], denoted “PWG” in the figures, is employed with three different sets of parton shower models, namely Pythia [19], Pythia8  [27] and Herwig [22]. The other NLO generator is MC@NLO [21] interfaced with the Herwig parton shower. Generators at the LO accuracy are represented by MadGraph  [29] interfaced with Pythia for parton showering, which calculates \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
